result.execSummary:
The defendant Antonio Rollins was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

02:54 PM Defendant Antonio Rollins in court, in custody with attorney Alexander J. Kostal.  Jane E. Kohlwey appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Cases called: 15CM227 & 15CM424. Court found a conflict in 15CM424. Defendant waived the confict. Rights/Elements. Defendant pled no contest to Ct. 2 of 15CM227 and to Ct. 3 of 15CM424. Court found guilty. Judgment was entered. All remaining charges dismissed and read in. In both cases Court withheld sentencing, placed the defendant on probation for 2 years, concurrent to each other, but consecutive to the sentence currently serving. Conditions of probation include: Maintain absolute sobriety. $543.00 costs in 15CM227 and $443.00 costs in 15CM424. Complete domestic abuse counseling. Submit DNA sample. Cash bond to be applied towards costs. Atty Kostal requested bond be returned. Court denied the request. Stipulation to be filed for jail credit due. 3:16 PM
